  "instructions": [
    "Heat the Instant Pot on the saut\u00e9 setting and add olive oil.",
    "Saut\u00e9 onion, garlic, carrot, and celery until the vegetables soften, about 3\u20114 minutes.",
    "Add the white wine, deglaze the pot, and let it reduce for 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in the stock and stir. Add the bay leaf, salt, pepper, and lemon juice. Seal the lid and set to pressure cook on high for 5 minutes.",
    "Quick release the pressure, then add the salmon cubes and fresh mint. Taste and adjust seasoning. Cook on saut\u00e9 for 3 minutes, or until the salmon flakes easily.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with extra mint if desired. Enjoy a comforting, herb\u2011infused American salmon stew."
